---
import { Picture } from 'astro:assets';
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import measurementCaliper from '../assets/images/measurement-caliper.jpg';
---

<BaseLayout
    title="Capping Chuck Troubleshooting & Calibration Guide"
    description="Diagnostic procedures for capping chuck and headset issues: cap scuffing, torque scatter, stripped TE bands, cross-threading, vacuum loss, and undertorque. Calibration steps and fix procedures."
    canonical="https://cappingchucks.com/troubleshooting/"
    ogTitle="Troubleshooting & Calibration | CappingChucks.com"
    ogDescription="Capping chuck troubleshooting guide. Diagnostics and fixes for scuffing, torque variation, TE band failures, cross-threading, and undertorque."
    schemaType="TechArticle"
    breadcrumb="Troubleshooting"
>
    <header class="pt-20 pb-12 border-b border-border">
        <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6 pb-4">
            <p class="font-mono text-[0.7rem] text-teal-700 tracking-wider uppercase mb-2"><a href="/" class="no-underline hover:underline">Home</a> / Troubleshooting</p>
            <h1 class="mb-4">Troubleshooting & Calibration</h1>
            <p class="text-lg text-ink-light leading-relaxed max-w-xl">Common capping line issues, root causes, and corrective procedures. Covers both <a href="/chuck-types/">chuck</a> and <a href="/capping-headsets/">headset</a> failures.</p>
        </div>
        <figure class="mx-auto max-w-4xl px-6">
            <Picture
                src={measurementCaliper}
                alt="Mitutoyo digital caliper measuring steel beam width for dimensional verification"
                class="w-full h-56 sm:h-72 object-cover object-center rounded-lg"
                widths={[600, 900, 1200]}
                sizes="100vw"
                formats={['avif', 'webp']}
                quality={80}
                loading="eager"
            />
            <figcaption class="mt-2 font-mono text-[0.68rem] text-ink-faint">Dimensional verification with a digital caliper. Photo: Pexels</figcaption>
        </figure>
    </header>

    <main>
        <section class="py-16 border-b border-border">
            <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
                <span class="section-rule"></span>
                <h2 class="mb-6">Issue Diagnostics</h2>

                <div class="overflow-x-auto">
                    <table>
                        <thead>
                            <tr>
                                <th>Issue</th>
                                <th>Likely Cause</th>
                                <th>Fix</th>
                            </tr>
                        </thead>
                        <tbody>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Cap Scuffing</td>
                                <td>Excessive radial grip force or misaligned bore. The closure shell abrades against the chuck's <a href="/glossary/#knurling">knurl</a> pattern during rotation.</td>
                                <td>Reduce grip pressure or replace worn insert. Verify bore ID matches closure OD within &plusmn;0.15mm. Replace urethane liner if scuffed.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Inconsistent Torque (High CV%)</td>
                                <td>Worn clutch plates, contaminated hysteresis disc, or unstable pneumatic supply pressure. Also check incoming closure and container finish dimensions.</td>
                                <td>Replace clutch plates or clean the hysteresis assembly. Verify pneumatic supply at the machine's specified pressure (typical: 6.0 bar &plusmn;0.2 bar) with a working moisture trap. If variation persists, run a Cpk study on incoming closures and finishes.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Stripped TE Bands</td>
                                <td>Over-torque causing the closure to rotate past the <a href="/glossary/#bridge-count">bridge</a> fracture point. Bridges shear during application instead of at first opening.</td>
                                <td>Reduce application torque 10 to 15%. Verify bridge count and thickness against the closure spec. Check chuck runout for uneven axial loading.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Cross-Threading</td>
                                <td>Closure not centered on the finish before thread engagement. Worn guide rails, wrong chuck height, or vacuum pick failure in cap feed.</td>
                                <td>Check chuck descent height and pre-thread contact point. Inspect the centering bell for wear. Confirm container-finish perpendicularity (tilt under 1&deg;) against the container drawing.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Vacuum Loss Post-Capping</td>
                                <td>Not enough torque for full seal compression. Could also be damaged liner or out-of-spec container finish (chipped or ovalized).</td>
                                <td>Increase torque in 0.2 N&middot;m steps until headspace vacuum hits spec. Check the finish sealing surface with go/no-go gauges.</td>
                            </tr>
                            <tr>
                                <td>Undertorque</td>
                                <td>Clutch slipping below target due to worn friction surfaces, weak spring, or hysteresis coil degradation. Contamination on clutch interfaces drops the friction coefficient.</td>
                                <td>Replace clutch disc and spring. Degrease all contact surfaces. On <a href="/capping-headsets/#magnetic">hysteresis units</a>, verify coil resistance and current draw against spec. Audit all spindle stations.</td>
                            </tr>
                        </tbody>
                    </table>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section id="calibration" class="py-16 border-b border-border">
            <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
                <span class="section-rule"></span>
                <h2 class="mb-6">Calibration Procedure</h2>

                <div class="space-y-4 text-[0.95rem] text-ink-light">
                    <p>Set the target application torque from the closure manufacturer's spec. On <a href="/capping-headsets/#spring-clutch">spring-clutch headsets</a>, adjust the compression preload via the threaded collar or shim stack. On <a href="/capping-headsets/#magnetic">magnetic hysteresis headsets</a>, adjust the DC current to the coil.</p>

                    <p>Verify with a calibrated torque analyzer using your validated sample size. Calculate CV%. High-speed rotary lines run tighter targets (&le; 3%) than inline (&le; 5%). If variation runs over your limit, check for worn clutch surfaces, spindle-coupling backlash, or out-of-spec incoming closures.</p>
                </div>

                <div class="spec-panel mt-8">
                    <h3 class="mb-3 text-sm">Calibration Parameters</h3>
                    <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-label">Sample Size</span><span class="spec-value">30+ closures (per validation procedure)</span></div>
                    <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-label">CV% Target</span><span class="spec-value">&le; 5% standard, &le; 3% on high-speed rotary</span></div>
                    <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-label">High-Speed Lines</span><span class="spec-value">Tighter CV%, more frequent torque audits</span></div>
                    <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-label">Torque Analyzer</span><span class="spec-value">Calibrated, with a documented method</span></div>
                    <div class="spec-row"><span class="spec-label">Verification Basis</span><span class="spec-value">Closure supplier, customer, regulatory, and plant requirements (see <a href="https://store.astm.org/d2063_d2063m-24.html" rel="noopener" target="_blank">ASTM D2063</a>)</span></div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="py-16 pb-20">
            <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl px-6">
                <span class="section-rule"></span>
                <h2 class="mb-4">Related</h2>
                <ul class="space-y-3 text-[0.92rem]">
                    <li><a href="/chuck-types/">Capping Chuck Types</a> -- understand the mechanism before diagnosing the failure</li>
                    <li><a href="/capping-headsets/">Capping Headsets</a> -- headset-level torque control and maintenance</li>
                    <li><a href="/glossary/">Glossary</a> -- definitions for torque, slip torque, CV%, and related terms</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </section>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
